{"id": "duc04-testb-13:5#15", "contents": "A snooker game between longtime Asian rivals India and Pakistan at the Asian Games led to a flareup of tempers on Sunday, showcasing the depth of differences between the two nations. The incident began when a Thai referee ruled that India's Yashin Merchant had committed a foul during a decisive frame, sparking a fierce debate with the referee that forced a 15-minute stoppage of play. Merchant eventually defeated Mohammad Saleh 5-4 after order was restored, but the incident highlighted the distrust between the two neighbors that often spills over into sports."}
